@Mamba4ever

I agree with Marko997, in most cases, 720p & 1080p encodes are almost indistinguishable on the iPad 3. Despite it's resolution being higher than even 1080p, the iPad 3's scaler does superb work.

Now, a lot depends on the encode, and on the source material, but I think the best bang for your (bit) buck is with 720p encodes.
